    "updated_at": "2025-10-22T08:10:51Z",
    "body": "I'm also getting this when running starship on a Chromebook \"in Linux\". For those who don't know \"Linux\" on Chromebooks (aka Crostini) is a VM that runs LXD which runs a Debian container with a few modifications.\n\nEdit: I'm running the default configuration and I expected the simple \"❯\" prompt.\n\nEdit 2: I solved my problem. I'm using a dotfile manager (chezmoi) and configure starship to disable the container module when using my dotfile configuration inside a container. That should be good for now.",
